<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="10" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d10">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">710.1012 Anti-War/79a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Argentine Minister for Foreign Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Saavedra Lamas</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-28">April 28, 1934</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>On the occasion of the signing of the Anti-War Pact by 13 additional
                            countries allow me to congratulate you most heartily on your splendid
                            efforts for the promotion of pacific settlement of international
                            disputes.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cordell Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>